This paper is primarily focused on game-theoretic models of information retrieval, which falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the utility schemes of authors and their learning dynamics, which are topics related to Game Theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of ranking methods, which could be classified under Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses convergence of learning dynamics, which is a topic related to Machine Learning (cs.LG).
